&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.limericktango.com/blog/&#34;&gt;Limerick&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;s post on &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.limericktango.com/2008/11/boleos/&#34;&gt;boleos&lt;/a&gt; made me think of the concept of boleos helados, or frozen boleos. I went to a workshop with Chicho and Lucía a couple of years back, and while the frozen boleos were sort of fun, it ruins your boleo technique if you shape your boleos that way. Methinks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The intrigueing thing about boleos is their free flowing unmanaged quality. Or as Limerick says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;You don’t do boleos, boleos happen.&lt;/blockquote&gt;
